[{"id":36229,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>14</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Given,</p><p>Equation of the curves <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;</p><p>Now for parabola&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>, equation of tangent is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Which is also&nbsp;tangent to parabola&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>,</p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;will satisfy the curve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>,</p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>mx</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>64</mn><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>64</mn><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Now making discriminant zero we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>64</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, the equation of tangent is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Now distance of point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;from the tangent will be,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>9</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":36268,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>53</mn></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>53</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>53</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Tangent at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></math>, using Cartesian form.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Equation of circle</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>It passes through&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>13</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>Circle is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>13</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>52</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>13</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>52</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>32</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>53</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>48</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;Centre is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>53</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":36204,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["$\\tan ^{-1}\\left(\\frac{4}{5}\\right)$","$\\tan ^{-1}\\left(\\frac{9}{7}\\right)$","$\\tan ^{-1}\\left(\\frac{11}{9}\\right)$","$\\frac{\\pi}{2}-\\tan ^{-1}\\left(\\frac{3}{2}\\right)$"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/rPQU_5KkhTKucCcb-Uxpt4_QWullcQgoXsh4hpdnCS8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n\n\n\n$\\begin{aligned} & 3 x-2 y+12=0 \\\\ & 4 y=3 x^2 \\\\ & \\therefore 2(3 x+12)=3 x^2 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow x^2-2 x-8=0 \\\\ & \\Rightarrow x=-2,4 \\\\ & \\mathrm{~m}_{\\mathrm{OA}}=-3 / 2, \\mathrm{~m}_{\\mathrm{OB}}=3 \\\\ & \\tan \\theta=\\left(\\frac{\\frac{-3}{2}-3}{1-\\frac{9}{2}}\\right)=\\frac{9}{7} \\\\ & \\theta=\\tan ^{-1}\\left(\\frac{9}{7}\\right) \\text { (angle will be acute) }\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":36284,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["<math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>Î¸</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi>Î¸</mi></math>","<math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>Î¸</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi>Î¸</mi></math>","<math><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi>Î¸</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>Î¸</mi></math>","<math><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi>Î¸</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>Î¸</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>As we know, if the line <math><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math> is a tangent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>y</mi></math>, then <math><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p><p>So, equation of tangent with slope <math><mi>m</mi></math> is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mi>i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Since, tangent is inclined at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi></math> with the positive <math><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo></math> axis, i.e.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>tan</mi><mo>&#8289;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></math>.</p><p>Equation of tangent is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#8289;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">cot</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mrow></math></p><p><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>y</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":36184,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["$2(8-3 \\sqrt{3})$","$2(3+\\sqrt{3})$","$4(6+\\sqrt{3})$","$4(3-\\sqrt{3})$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Parabola $y^2 = 4x$ has vertex $O = (0,0)$. By symmetry, let $A = (t^2, 2t)$, $B = (t^2, -2t)$.<br>$OA = t\\sqrt{t^2+4}$, $AB = 4t$.<br>For equilateral: $OA = AB \\Rightarrow t\\sqrt{t^2+4} = 4t \\Rightarrow t^2 = 12 \\Rightarrow t = 2\\sqrt{3}$.<br>$A = (12, 4\\sqrt{3})$, $B = (12, -4\\sqrt{3})$.<br>Circle with $AB$ as diameter: centre $(12, 0)$, radius $= 4\\sqrt{3}$.<br>Minimum distance from origin $= 12 - 4\\sqrt{3} = 4(3 - \\sqrt{3})$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":36252,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given, Parabola&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;and circle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c207ecc1-93ee-40d3-a9cc-e37eb5553543-image.png\" style=\"width: 257px; height: 214px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;Parabola&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;at point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Differentiating&nbsp;w .r. t.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mmultiscripts><mi>x</mi><none></none><mo>&#39;</mo><mprescripts></mprescripts><none></none><mo>&#39;</mo></mmultiscripts></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><menclose notation=\"left\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></menclose></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Equation of tangent</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Line L is&nbsp;also tangent to the circle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>a</mi></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>a</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mi>a</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":36265,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"Slope of tangent&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mi>T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi></math><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Equation:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8757;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p>Point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> will not lie on it</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":36208,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/GEmbLsLDZ-Av-6U62mdJIQT22iboc2hQNQGl3ugyir0.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$\\begin{aligned}\n& T=S_1 \\\\\n& x_1+y_1=x_1^2+y_1^2 \\\\\n& \\alpha x_1=x_1^2+y_1^2 \\\\\n& \\alpha\\left(2 t^2\\right)=4 t^4+16 t^2 \\\\\n& \\alpha=2 t^2+8 \\\\\n& \\frac{\\alpha-8}{2}=t^2\n\\end{aligned}$<br />Also, $4 \\mathrm{t}^4+16 \\mathrm{t}^2-4 < 0$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{t}^2=-2+\\sqrt{5} \\\\\n& \\alpha=4+2 \\sqrt{5} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\alpha \\in(8,4+2 \\sqrt{5}) \\\\\n& \\therefore(2 \\mathrm{q}-\\mathrm{p})^2=80\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":36294,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Parabola","question":"","options":["$3(x+y)+4=0$","$8(2 x+y)+3=0$","$4(x+y)+3=0$","$x+2 y+3=0$"],"answer":2,"solution":"As origin is the only common point to $x-$ axis and $y$-axis, so, origin is the common vertex Let the equation of two of parabolas be $y^2=4 a x$ and $x^2=4 b y$\nNow latus rectum of both parabolas $=3$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\therefore 4 a=4 b=3 \\\\\n&\\Rightarrow a=b=\\frac{3}{4}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n$\\therefore$ Two parabolas are $y^2=3 x$ and $x^2=3 y$ Suppose $y=m x+c$ is the common tangent.\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\therefore y^2=3 x \\Rightarrow(m x+c)^2=3 x \\\\\n&\\Rightarrow m^2 x^2+(2 m c-3) x+c^2=0\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nAs, the tangent touches at one point only\nSo, $b^2-4 a c=0$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\Rightarrow(2 m c-3)^2-4 m^2 c^2=0 \\\\\n&\\Rightarrow 4 m^2 c^2+9-12 m c-4 m^2 c^2=0\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\Rightarrow c=\\frac{9}{12 m}=\\frac{3}{4 m} \\\\\n&\\therefore x^2=3 y \\Rightarrow x^2=3(m x+c) \\\\\n&\\Rightarrow x^2-3 m x-3 c=0\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nForm (i) and ( ii)\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&m^2=\\frac{-4 c}{3}=\\frac{-4}{3}\\left(\\frac{3}{4 m}\\right) \\\\\n&\\Rightarrow m^3=-1 \\Rightarrow m=-1 \\Rightarrow c=\\frac{-3}{4}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nHence, $y=m x+c=-x-\\frac{3}{4}$\n$$\n\\Rightarrow 4(x+y)+3=0\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null}]